 minority education, as well as to junior and senior researchers in those fields.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aBilingualismxStudy and teaching. 0aEducation, Bilingual. 0aLanguage and languagesxStudy and teachingxBilingual method. 0aLanguage planning. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aBilingual education.  aIndigenous education.  aIndigenous language endangerment and revitalization.  aLanguage minority education.  aLanguage planning.  aLanguage rights.  aMultilingual education.  aRichard Ruiz.1 aBaker, Colin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBever, Olga, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarroll, Kevin S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCombs, Mary Carol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCruz, D. Lane Santa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGalla, Candace Kaleimamoowahinekapu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGilmore, Perry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGonzález, Norma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGonzález, Ángela Pamela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHornberger, Nancy H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHornberger, Nancy H., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aIddings, Ana Christina Da Silva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJiménez-Quispe, Luz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Eric J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Janelle M., econtributor.4ctb4ht